In this speech, President Joe Biden welcomes Muslim Americans to the White House to celebrate Eid. He acknowledges the diverse contributions of Muslims to the nation and highlights their presence in various fields such as education, medicine, law, business, and politics. The President recognizes Muslim athletes, cultural influences, and the increasing representation of Muslim Americans in Congress. He also mentions members of his administration who are Muslim and their contributions to the country. President Biden emphasizes the importance of combating Islamophobia and standing up against all forms of hate. He expresses his commitment to building peace and advocating for the rights and dignity of all people. The President concludes by celebrating the diversity of America and the shared values that unite its citizens.